\section*{4) Planning a Survey (Process of Conducting a Survey)}
- Good surveys start with clear theory, then the translation of theory into sensible survey questions, pre-testing and revision of questions, development and pre-testing of the survey instrument, sampling, data gathering, and, finally, data analysis. The processes are:
- Define the purpose of the survey

