- Ensuring health sector contribution to the country's development
- Recognizes the need to facilitate provision of health promotion and targeted disease prevention/curative services through community based initiatives as defined in the 2006 Community Health Strategy.
- The concept of community strategy came about after seeing the need to enhance community access to health care in order to improve productivity and reduce poverty, hunger and child \& maternal dearth as well as improve education performance across all stages of the life cycle
- Kenya realized the need of establishing sustainable and decentralized community level services and accountability

